  ('a0000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000132', v_user, '2026-04-19', '120', 'motivated', 'Double session. WMF three-quarters done. Blade Itself — the tournament at Adua is brilliantly staged.', NULL, NULL, '2026-04-19 14:00:00+00'),
  ('a0000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000133', v_user, '2026-04-20', '50', 'motivated', 'Blade Itself accelerating. The truth about Bayaz''s nature beginning to surface. Sinister doesn''t cover it.', NULL, NULL, '2026-04-20 21:00:00+00'),
  ('a0000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000134', v_user, '2026-04-21', '45', 'thoughtful', 'WMF approaching the end. Kvothe''s naming skill emerging fully. The wonder and the dread are balanced perfectly.', NULL, NULL, '2026-04-21 21:30:00+00'),
  ('a0000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000135', v_user, '2026-04-22', '60', 'moved', 'Blade Itself — Glokta''s final scheme. The pragmatism of this book is almost terrifying in how plausible it feels.', NULL, NULL, '2026-04-22 21:00:00+00'),
  ('a0000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000136', v_user, '2026-04-23', '45', 'thoughtful', 'WMF nearing its close. Rothfuss writes the goodbye chapters with the same care as the hello ones.', NULL, NULL, '2026-04-23 21:00:00+00'),
  ('a0000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000137', v_user, '2026-04-24', '50', 'moved', 'Blade Itself ending — the journey north begins. Already ordered Before They Are Hanged.', NULL, NULL, '2026-04-24 21:30:00+00'),
  ('a0000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000138', v_user, '2026-04-25', '90', 'moved', 'Finished The Blade Itself on a Saturday afternoon. Abercrombie earned every note of that ending.', NULL, NULL, '2026-04-25 15:00:00+00'),
  ('a0000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000139', v_user, '2026-04-26', '120', 'moved', 'WMF nearing 90%. Also cracked open Before They Are Hanged — could not wait a single day.', NULL, NULL, '2026-04-26 14:00:00+00'),
  ('a0000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000140', v_user, '2026-04-27', '45', 'thoughtful', 'WMF reaching its final mysteries. Kvothe''s silence in the frame story feels like the answer to everything.', NULL, NULL, '2026-04-27 21:00:00+00'),
  ('a0000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000141', v_user, '2026-04-28', '50', 'thoughtful', 'Before They Are Hanged opens mid-journey. Abercrombie drops you into the chaos of multiple wars at once.', NULL, NULL, '2026-04-28 21:30:00+00'),
  ('a0000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000142', v_user, '2026-04-29', '45', 'moved', 'WMF almost done. The Chandrian encounter — brief, devastating, withholding. Rothfuss at his cruelest.', NULL, NULL, '2026-04-29 21:00:00+00'),
  ('a0000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000143', v_user, '2026-04-30', '60', 'moved', 'WMF final chapters. The third day of Kvothe''s story still unwritten. The longing this creates is immense.', NULL, NULL, '2026-04-30 21:00:00+00'),
  ('a0000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000144', v_user, '2026-05-01', '90', 'moved', 'Finished The Wise Man''s Fear on a Saturday. A 994-page book that still feels too short. Outstanding.', NULL, NULL, '2026-05-01 15:00:00+00'),
  ('a0000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000145', v_user, '2026-05-02', '120', 'thoughtful', 'Sunday deeply into Before They Are Hanged. Three storylines, three wars, and Abercrombie manages them all.', NULL, NULL, '2026-05-02 14:00:00+00'),
  ('a0000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000146', v_user, '2026-05-03', '45', 'thoughtful', 'Logen''s group beyond the edge of the world. The desolation of the Empty Lands is beautifully rendered.', NULL, NULL, '2026-05-03 21:00:00+00'),
  ('a0000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000147', v_user, '2026-05-04', '50', 'happy', 'Dogman narrating. His working-class pragmatism cuts through the epic like a blade. Such a good choice.', NULL, NULL, '2026-05-04 21:30:00+00'),
  ('a0000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000148', v_user, '2026-05-05', '45', 'moved', 'Glokta in Dagoska. The colonial administration scenes feel horribly, uncomfortably contemporary.', NULL, NULL, '2026-05-05 21:00:00+00'),
  ('a0000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000149', v_user, '2026-05-06', '50', 'thoughtful', 'Jezal''s transformation continues. He''s becoming someone worth caring about, which I didn''t think possible.', NULL, NULL, '2026-05-06 21:00:00+00'),
  ('a0000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000150', v_user, '2026-05-07', '45', 'thoughtful', 'The quest party dynamic reminds me of Tolkien by way of nihilism — fellowship without the comfort.', NULL, NULL, '2026-05-07 21:30:00+00'),
  ('a0000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000151', v_user, '2026-05-08', '50', 'moved', 'Logen''s group deep in the frozen north. The isolation is claustrophobic and entirely effective.', NULL, NULL, '2026-05-08 21:00:00+00'),
  ('a0000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000152', v_user, '2026-05-09', '45', 'thoughtful', 'The siege of Dagoska tightens. Glokta''s choices here are impossible and he makes them anyway.', NULL, NULL, '2026-05-09 21:30:00+00'),
  ('a0000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000153', v_user, '2026-05-10', '90', 'thoughtful', 'Saturday morning session. The quest party dynamics shifting — Jezal is not who he was.', NULL, NULL, '2026-05-10 10:00:00+00'),
  ('a0000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000154', v_user, '2026-05-10', '60', 'thoughtful', 'Bayaz''s patience is terrifying. He is the longest game of all, and you feel it in every scene.', NULL, NULL, '2026-05-10 20:00:00+00'),
  ('a0000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000155', v_user, '2026-05-11', '90', 'moved', 'Sunday read. The confrontation in the ruins. Abercrombie subverts every heroic expectation with surgical precision.', NULL, NULL, '2026-05-11 14:00:00+00'),
  ('a0000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000156', v_user, '2026-05-12', '45', 'moved', 'The loss of Dagoska. Glokta''s exit from the city is heartbreaking and grubby at once.', NULL, NULL, '2026-05-12 21:00:00+00'),
  ('a0000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000157', v_user, '2026-05-13', '50', 'thoughtful', 'Jezal changed. Logen changing. Only Glokta remains constant — a constant of pain and pragmatism.', NULL, NULL, '2026-05-13 21:30:00+00'),
  ('a0000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000158', v_user, '2026-05-14', '45', 'moved', 'Racing toward the end of Book 2. The "heroes" aren''t winning and the cost just keeps mounting.', NULL, NULL, '2026-05-14 21:00:00+00'),
  ('a0000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000159', v_user, '2026-05-15', '60', 'moved', 'Almost done with Before They Are Hanged. The foreshadowing in the title lands fully now.', NULL, NULL, '2026-05-15 21:00:00+00'),
  ('a0000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000160', v_user, '2026-05-16', '120', 'moved', 'Finished Before They Are Hanged on a Saturday morning. The ending is bleak and brilliant. Started Last Argument immediately.', NULL, NULL, '2026-05-16 10:30:00+00'),
  ('a0000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000161', v_user, '2026-05-16', '60', 'thoughtful', 'Evening session. Last Argument of Kings opens with war already lost in so many ways. Abercrombie''s winter has arrived.', NULL, NULL, '2026-05-16 20:00:00+00'),
  ('a0000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000162', v_user, '2026-05-17', '90', 'moved', 'Sunday. Jezal''s sudden elevation. The cruelty of that chapter — what power actually looks like up close.', NULL, NULL, '2026-05-17 14:00:00+00'),
  ('a0000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000163', v_user, '2026-05-18', '45', 'moved', 'Logen and the Bloody Nine struggling for control of the same body. Brilliant, disturbing writing.', NULL, NULL, '2026-05-18 21:00:00+00'),
  ('a0000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000164', v_user, '2026-05-19', '50', 'thoughtful', 'The politics of the Union deteriorating. Abercrombie gives no one clean hands — not even the reader.', NULL, NULL, '2026-05-19 21:30:00+00'),
  ('a0000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000165', v_user, '2026-05-20', '45', 'thoughtful', 'Glokta''s assignment worse than any torture he''s administered. The irony is devastating.', NULL, NULL, '2026-05-20 21:00:00+00'),
  ('a0000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000166', v_user, '2026-05-21', '50', 'moved', 'Sand dan Glokta in charge of the city''s defense. Grimly perfect.', NULL, NULL, '2026-05-21 21:30:00+00'),
  ('a0000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000167', v_user, '2026-05-22', '45', 'motivated', 'The Battle of Adua beginning. I cancelled plans to keep reading.', NULL, NULL, '2026-05-22 20:00:00+00'),
  ('a0000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000168', v_user, '2026-05-23', '90', 'thoughtful', 'Saturday morning. The Gurkish siege of Adua. Abercrombie''s war is unheroic and exact.', NULL, NULL, '2026-05-23 10:00:00+00'),
  ('a0000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000169', v_user, '2026-05-23', '60', 'motivated', 'The Bloody Nine unleashed. Read that chapter twice. Horrifying and magnificent at the same time.', NULL, NULL, '2026-05-23 20:00:00+00'),
  ('a0000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000170', v_user, '2026-05-24', '90', 'thoughtful', 'Sunday. Jezal on the battlefield — not a hero, but unable to be a coward either.', NULL, NULL, '2026-05-24 14:00:00+00'),
  ('a0000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000171', v_user, '2026-05-25', '45', 'moved', 'Bayaz and the revelation of the First Law. Everything restructured in one breathtaking sequence.', NULL, NULL, '2026-05-25 21:00:00+00'),
  ('a0000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000172', v_user, '2026-05-26', '50', 'thoughtful', 'The ending approaches. Reading slowly to absorb every consequence.', NULL, NULL, '2026-05-26 21:30:00+00'),
  ('a0000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000173', v_user, '2026-05-27', '45', 'moved', 'Glokta''s ultimate compromise. In any other book unforgivable. Here it feels like survival.', NULL, NULL, '2026-05-27 21:00:00+00'),
  ('a0000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000174', v_user, '2026-05-28', '50', 'moved', '"You have to be realistic about these things." One of the great last lines in fantasy.', NULL, NULL, '2026-05-28 21:00:00+00'),
  ('a0000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000175', v_user, '2026-05-29', '50', 'thoughtful', 'The aftermath chapters. Nobody got what they wanted. Somehow that feels completely true.', NULL, NULL, '2026-05-29 21:30:00+00'),
  ('a0000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000176', v_user, '2026-05-30', '90', 'thoughtful', 'Saturday morning. Final chapters. The First Law has dismantled every fantasy trope I arrived with.', NULL, NULL, '2026-05-30 10:30:00+00'),
  ('a0000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000177', v_user, '2026-05-30', '60', 'moved', 'Last pages. Already ordered The Lies of Locke Lamora.', NULL, NULL, '2026-05-30 20:00:00+00'),
  ('a0000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000178', v_user, '2026-05-31', '120', 'moved', 'Finished Last Argument of Kings! The trilogy ending is perfect. Started Locke Lamora immediately — needed something new.', NULL, NULL, '2026-05-31 11:00:00+00'),
  ('a0000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000179', v_user, '2026-05-31', '60', 'happy', 'Camorr is extraordinary. The glass towers, the canals, the thieves'' cant. Completely vivid.', NULL, NULL, '2026-05-31 20:00:00+00'),
  ('a0000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000180', v_user, '2026-06-01', '50', 'happy', 'The Gentleman Bastards as a crew. Locke is wildly likeable and obviously going to suffer for it.', NULL, NULL, '2026-06-01 21:00:00+00'),
  ('a0000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000181', v_user, '2026-06-02', '45', 'happy', 'The elaborate flashback structure. Lynch uses it beautifully to build suspense without withholding unfairly.', NULL, NULL, '2026-06-02 21:30:00+00'),
  ('a0000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000182', v_user, '2026-06-03', '50', 'happy', 'The Grey King. Locke is playing above his weight and knows it. The fun is watching him improvise.', NULL, NULL, '2026-06-03 21:00:00+00'),
  ('a0000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000183', v_user, '2026-06-04', '60', 'happy', 'The con within the con. Lynch''s plotting is intricate without ever feeling artificial.', NULL, NULL, '2026-06-04 21:00:00+00'),
  ('9401430f-e086-4d21-90ed-736a1fe04e01', v_user, '2026-06-05', '44', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2026-06-05 08:24:06.328+00'),
  ('a0000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000184', v_user, '2026-06-05', '45', 'moved', 'The revelation of who the Grey King is. I should have guessed and didn''t. Excellent.', NULL, NULL, '2026-06-05 21:00:00+00'),
  ('a0000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000185', v_user, '2026-06-06', '90', 'moved', 'Saturday morning. Locke''s grief is real and Scott Lynch doesn''t let us look away from it.', NULL, NULL, '2026-06-06 10:00:00+00'),
  ('a0000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000186', v_user, '2026-06-06', '60', 'moved', 'Camorr in the rain. This book is genuinely funny and genuinely devastating in equal measure.', NULL, NULL, '2026-06-06 20:00:00+00'),
  ('a0000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000187', v_user, '2026-06-07', '90', 'moved', 'Sunday morning. The confrontation building. I''m rationing chapters. Don''t want this to end.', NULL, NULL, '2026-06-07 10:00:00+00'),
  ('a0000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000188', v_user, '2026-06-07', '120', 'moved', 'Sunday afternoon. Almost done with Locke Lamora. The price of the final victory is enormous.', NULL, NULL, '2026-06-07 15:00:00+00'),
  ('a0281b3d-06e8-446d-8265-b445be06d163', v_user, '2026-06-08', '45', 'motivated', 'Great spice-fueled evening read.', 'Fear is the mind-killer.', '12', '2026-06-08 16:37:15.989+00'),
  ('a0000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000189', v_user, '2026-06-08', '50', 'moved', 'Finished The Lies of Locke Lamora. Outstanding. Started Assassin''s Apprentice for a complete change of tone.', NULL, NULL, '2026-06-08 21:00:00+00'),
  ('fd4f7212-e9be-4312-94b7-0e79c3434b62', v_user, '2026-06-09', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2026-06-09 13:25:28.251+00'),
  ('a0000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000190', v_user, '2026-06-09', '45', 'thoughtful', 'Fitz is immediately compelling — the bastard son perspective is handled with such care by Hobb.', NULL, NULL, '2026-06-09 21:00:00+00'),
  ('a0000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000191', v_user, '2026-06-10', '50', 'thoughtful', 'The Skill and the Wit. Hobb''s magic systems are psychological, not mechanical. Very different from Sanderson.', NULL, NULL, '2026-06-10 21:30:00+00'),
  ('a0000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000192', v_user, '2026-06-11', '45', 'thoughtful', 'Palace politics. Hobb makes court intrigue feel genuinely dangerous, not glamorous.', NULL, NULL, '2026-06-11 21:00:00+00'),
  ('a0000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000193', v_user, '2026-06-12', '60', 'thoughtful', 'Fitz''s relationship with Chade. The assassin-teacher dynamic is unsettling and tender at once.', NULL, NULL, '2026-06-12 21:00:00+00'),
  ('a0000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000194', v_user, '2026-06-13', '90', 'moved', 'Finished Assassin''s Apprentice on a Saturday morning. Robin Hobb is extraordinary. Starting A Clash of Kings.', NULL, NULL, '2026-06-13 11:00:00+00'),
  ('a0000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000195', v_user, '2026-06-13', '60', 'thoughtful', 'Into A Clash of Kings. Martin''s world after Ned''s death feels genuinely unstable and full of menace.', NULL, NULL, '2026-06-13 20:00:00+00'),
  ('a0000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000196', v_user, '2026-06-14', '90', 'thoughtful', 'Sunday morning. Starting Oathbringer alongside Clash of Kings — two completely different epics at once.', NULL, NULL, '2026-06-14 10:00:00+00'),
  ('a0000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000197', v_user, '2026-06-14', '90', 'moved', 'Theon''s arc in Clash begins. Martin is brilliant at making you understand people you shouldn''t sympathize with.', NULL, NULL, '2026-06-14 19:00:00+00'),
  ('a0000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000198', v_user, '2026-06-15', '60', 'moved', 'Dalinar''s visions in Oathbringer are extraordinary. The history of Roshar is vast and strange.', NULL, NULL, '2026-06-15 10:00:00+00'),
